# YAML 1.2
# Citation File Format 1.2.0 — https://citation-file-format.github.io
#
# Why this file: research showed that academic citation tools (Zotero,
# the GitHub "Cite this repository" button) AND modern AI engines
# (ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity) extract structured author/version/title
# data from CITATION.cff when answering "who made X" / "how do I cite X"
# queries. Cheap to maintain, real upside for discoverability.
#
# Keep `date-released` + `version` synced with each tagged release.
# The `repository-code` URL is the canonical machine-readable handle;
# `url` is the human entry point.
cff-version: 1.2.0
title: Patens
abstract: >
  Patens is a browser-native, MIT-licensed type design editor with a
  94-rule audit module that explains every finding in plain English.
  Sketch glyphs with pressure, trace to cubic Bézier contours, audit
  continuously, ship real OpenType — all in a browser tab, no install,
  no account. Designed to teach as it edits.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Alejandro
    family-names: Vizio
    email: hi@patens.design
    affiliation: Patens
    orcid: ''
identifiers:
  - type: url
    value: https://patens.design
    description: Canonical site
  - type: url
    value: https://github.com/alevizio/patens
    description: Source repository
repository-code: https://github.com/alevizio/patens
url: https://patens.design
license: MIT
keywords:
  - type design
  - typography
  - font editor
  - opentype
  - browser-native
  - audit
  - bezier
  - variable fonts
  - color fonts
  - svelte
  - sveltekit
version: 1.5.2
date-released: 2026-05-25
